 [FILES] Insecurity  Deputy National Chairman of the party, South, Revd. Mathew Ajibola Lawal gave the charge in Asaba while inaugurating the Delta State Executive Committee of the party led by Honourable Ese Cole. Reverend Lawal criticised the federal government for its failure in finding lasting solution to the insecurity in the land, particularly kidnapping, armed banditry and killing, saying the ugly state of affairs in the country was of grave concern to all Nigerians and the international community. National Vice Chairman, South East, Dr. Hope Iyke Ejes berated the APC led federal government over its poor handling of challenges confronting the nation. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .